A 100-bed capacity boys’ hostel at the Government Secondary School, Gboko in Benue State on Wednesday caught fire Prof. Dennis Ityavyar, the state Commissioner of Education confirmed the incident to the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) on Wednesday in Makurdi. It was learnt that the fire started at about 9:00 am when the students were already in class. However, no casualty was recorded from the inferno. The commissioner disclosed that there were indications that the fire was as a result of power surge, adding that details of the damage was yet to be ascertained. “Government Secondary School, Gboko boys hostels was gutted by fire around 9a.m. The students were in school at the time. “We believe it was an electricity surge, by tomorrow, we will give more comprehensive details on the incident “The fire affected only one of the boys hostel, it is a co-educational school for both male and female,” he said. These content links are provided by Content.ad. Both Content.ad and the web site upon which the links are displayed may receive compensation when readers click on these links. Some of the content you are redirected to may be sponsored content. View our privacy policy here. To learn how you can use Content.ad to drive visitors to your content or add this service to your site, please contact us at info@content.ad. Family-Friendly Content Only recommend family-friendly content Website owners select the type of content that appears in our units. However, if you would like to ensure that Content.ad always displays family-friendly content on this device, regardless of what site you are on, check the option below. Learn More Again, fire guts school in Anambra 11-year-old student killed as fire guts Anambra school hostel Properties damaged as fire guts school dormitory again in Anambra